DESCRIPTION:On Monday\, March 2nd\, the MBA and Graduate Programs Office w
 ill host our Spring 2026 Executive Speaker Series and we are excited to w
 elcome Jack Hanlon\, a Product Leader at Meta. In this role\, he leads te
 ams that develop state of the art generative AI models and translate them
  into products to benefit Meta’s 3.5B+ global users.\nThis engaging inter
 view-style discussion titled\,"Beyond the Hype: Preparing for an AI-Drive
 n Workplace" will be facilitated by Michael Hacker\, Director of SBUS Tec
 hnology Support Services at Montclair State University Feliciano School o
 f Business. This is a unique opportunity for students to gain valuable in
 sights into Mr. Hanlon’s career journey and hear firsthand perspectives o
 n the impact of AI on day-to-day business functions\, leadership\, strate
 gic decision-making\, and the evolving business landscape.\nDetails of th
 e event are as follows:\nLight Dinner and Reception - 5:30 PMPresentation
  - 6:00 PMQ&A - 6:45-7:00 PMUniversity Hall Conference Center - 7th Floor
 \n\nHosted by: Feliciano School of Business\n\nAdditional Information can
  be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12222171
