X-SOURCE:Montclair Public Library
DTSTART:20260302T233000Z
DTEND:20260303T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260302T000000Z
SUMMARY:Waste Not\, Want Not Collage Workshop
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nJoin professional painter Anna Berlin to learn about the 
 varied artists of the 20th century who helped make collage a fixed idea of 
 modern art and experiment with their techniques in class. We will begin 
 each two-hour class by looking at images of artworks and discussing them. 
 There will be a collage assignment for each class that responds to the 
 works and artists we shared. These assignments will also be possible to 
 make with items you can find in your home – highlighting the adaptability 
 and accessibility of the collage medium. Artists we will discuss include 
 Miriam Schapiro\, Melissa Meyer\, Hannah Höch\, Howardena Pindell\, Betye 
 Saar\, Ellsworth Kelly\, and Anne Ryan.\n\nA materials fee of $14 will be 
 charged at time of registration.  Registration is required.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Teen Room\, Montclair Bellevue Avenue Branch
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Arts & Crafts, Bellevue Avenue Branch
UID:LibCal-10306-16466399
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16466399
END:VEVENT
