DESCRIPTION:As immigration policies develop\, it is best to stay educated.
  Know your rights and responsibilities!\n \nJoin the New Jersey Consortiu
 m for Immigrant Children for a webinar on key legal and policy issues imp
 acting the Montclair community. Information will be provided on immigrati
 on statuses\, policy updates\, legal protections\, judicial vs. administr
 ative orders\, and understanding your rights if encountering law enforcem
 ent. Sessions are open for students\, family\, faculty\, and staff in bot
 h English and Spanish. \n \nThe New Jersey Consortium for Immigrant Child
 ren (NJCIC) is a state-wide legal and policy advocacy and education organ
 ization specializing in youth immigration. They provide objective legal r
 esources\, aid\, and advice on immigration rights.\n \nStudent & Family E
 nglish Session: March 4\, 2:00-3:15: https://us06web.zoom.us/webinar/regi
 ster/WN_iGJLl9ZWR7KXRUE_aniMsA\nStudent & Family Spanish Session: April 9
 \, 5:30-6:45:\nhttps://us06web.zoom.us/j/82724283081?pwd=KzAjQw24vxqmzbUR
 BXGmbBLV3V60m3.1\n\nHosted by: College for Education and Engaged Learning
 \, Government Relations and Community Affairs \, Office of Student Belong
 ing\, Office for Hispanic Initiatives\, Office of Community Engagement an
 d Partnerships\, The Office for Experiential Education and Career Connect
 ions\n\nOnline Location: https://us06web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_iGJL
 l9ZWR7KXRUE_aniMsA\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://mon
 tclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12262773
DTEND:20260304T201500Z
DTSTAMP:20260302T033127Z
DTSTART:20260304T190000Z
LOCATION:Online
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
