DESCRIPTION:Local Black and Latina professional women will critically refl
 ect on identity\, resilience\, self-esteem\, and leadership. Library reso
 urces and literature for support will be shared. Students\, staff\, facul
 ty\, and community members of all backgrounds are welcome to join. \nPane
 lists\nElaine Meryl Brown: Daytime Emmy® Award-winning writer and former 
 HBO media executive\, Elaine reflects on her experience within the media 
 and entertainment industry empowering Black women through her book The Ne
 xt Little Black Book of Success.\nCatherine Sackey: Policy Strategist\, S
 ystems Architect\, Founder and CEO of POP Consulting\, Catherine works to
  inspire women on their professional journeys.\nGladys Vonglahn: Original
 ly from Chile\, and a first-generation college student\, Gladys is a dete
 rmined and visionary leader as well as an expert on economic progress\, e
 ntrepreneurship\, self-esteem and personal improvement.\nRegister Here: h
 ttps://montclair.libcal.com/event/16399085\n\nHosted by: Sprague Library\
 n\nOnline Location: https://montclair.libcal.com/event/16399085\n\nAdditi
 onal Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage
 /event/12287699
