CATEGORIES:Sustainability
DESCRIPTION:Join the Environmental Club to hear from our guest speaker Amy
  Tuininga! Stop by to learn from on of your Montclair professors about re
 search\, sustainability programs and initiatives\, working in the industr
 y\, and more!\n \nDr. Amy Tuininga serves as the Associate Dean for Resea
 rch and Partnerships in the College of Science and Mathematics and is a t
 enured Full Professor in the Earth and Environmental Studies Department w
 ith doctoral faculty status.Currently\, she also is serving as the Interi
 m Director of the School of Computing. Her primary role is to support fac
 ulty and students in their research endeavors. She does this by growing p
 artnerships among faculty\, students\, administrators\, government agenci
 es\, private corporations\, and community groups to solve real-world prob
 lems. Projects involve aspects of the environment\, energy\, water\, food
 \, natural resources\, and economies that collectively function to build 
 sustainable communities. She is contributing to the College by sparking i
 nnovation in STEM research and promoting solutions for society’s most dif
 ficult challenges through academic-corporate-community partnerships. This
  work advances STEM and builds a resilient society that utilizes informed
 \, data-driven decision making\n\nHosted by: Environmental Club\n\nAdditi
 onal Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage
 /event/12293204
DTEND:20260304T201000Z
DTSTAMP:20260302T033127Z
DTSTART:20260304T191000Z
LOCATION:CELS 110
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Environmental Guest Speaker: Dr. Amy Tuininga
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12293204
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12293204
X-HOSTS:Environmental Club
