CATEGORIES:Social
DESCRIPTION:\nEver wonder how doctors can look at a patient\, hear a few s
 ymptoms\, and immediately start narrowing things down? This session is ab
 out how clinicians think\, not just what they memorize. In this workshop\
 , you’ll learn how medical professionals approach rapid diagnosis\, inclu
 ding how to identify key symptoms\, recognize red flags\, rule out unlike
 ly conditions\, and build a logical differential diagnosis under time pre
 ssure. Through guided case scenarios\, you’ll practice clinical reasoning
  the same way doctors are trained to systematically\, efficiently\, and w
 ithout guessing.\nThis is ideal for pre-med and pre-health students who w
 ant to strengthen their clinical mindset early\, but anyone interested in
  medical decision-making and problem-solving is welcome.\n\nHosted by: Me
 dical Case & Diagnostics Club \n\nAdditional Information can be found at:
  https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12293274
DTEND:20260304T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260302T033127Z
DTSTART:20260304T193000Z
LOCATION:University Hall 1070 - Phyllis & Gerald LeBoff Lecture Hall
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Think Like a Doctor: Rapid Diagnosis Workshop
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12293274
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12293274
X-HOSTS:Medical Case & Diagnostics Club
