X-SOURCE:Montclair Public Library
DTSTART:20260305T160000Z
DTEND:20260305T173000Z
DTSTAMP:20260305T000000Z
SUMMARY:NEW DATE: The Noodle Road: From Asia to Europe to America - Talk and Tasting NEW
DESCRIPTION:NEW CLASS DATE DUE TO WEATHER ON 2/23\n\nThis is a paid Adult 
 School class. Click here to register.\n\nThe event highlights an engaging 
 food experience that explores how noodles have traveled across continents 
 and connected cultures throughout history. Led by nutrition professionals\, 
 this session blends food history\, hands-on learning\, and delicious 
 tasting.\n\nWe will watch a short video\, followed by a lecture and an 
 interactive talk covering the story of noodles—where they originated\, 
 how noodle-making traditions spread along ancient trade routes\, and how 
 Eastern and Western noodle styles influenced each other. You will also 
 discover different kinds of noodles from around the world and learn what 
 makes each type unique.\n\nNext\, we will discuss how noodles can be a 
 nutritious choice by sharing tips on making healthier noodle-based meals\, 
 what to look for when choosing noodles (such as whole grains\, 
 ingredients\, and sodium content)\, and how to balance noodles with 
 vegetables and proteins. The event will conclude with a live cooking 
 demonstration of Korean hand-pulled noodles and fresh pasta made from 
 scratch\, followed by a tasting. Ingredient lists will be provided on the 
 day to ensure the safety of participants with food allergies or 
 sensitivities.\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Conference Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Culinary, Lectures / History & Culture
UID:LibCal-10306-16475121
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16475121
END:VEVENT
