SUMMARY:Rail\, Rail\, The Gang's All Here
DESCRIPTION:Metrotrails: NJ\, PA\, NY Metropolitan Area Hiking and More!\n
 "The West Essex Trail is a former railroad track bed of the Erie Lackawann
 a Railroad Caldwell Branch now hiking trail located mostly in Essex County
 \, New Jersey in the United States\, with a small section in Passaic Count
 y\, New Jersey."\nWe will be following the remainder of the branch that wa
 s sadly not converted to trail from the Passaic River as far as we can nor
 th to Bloomfield Ave\, Verona where the current trail starts then make our
  way back through parks and trails.\n\nOther points of interest: the gorge
 ous Grover Cleveland Park\, the Trotter Tract\, some of the Lenape Trail a
 nd some local parks. Route is subject to change.\n\nTotal mileage should b
 e under 10. There will be several opportunities for food in both direction
 s. This is a loop hike.\n\nRoute is approximately this:\nhttps://www.googl
 e.com/maps/d/edit?mid=1VxPj7usL7tQ2D3Txbhstw3ZjCBklbeE&usp=sharing
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/metrotrails/events/313432103/
