CREATED:20251216T211811Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260114T154831Z
UID:10005993-1772889300-1772897400@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Scout Program - Animal Program
DESCRIPTION:Scout Program – Animal Program \nSaturday March 7th \nTimes: 1:15-2:15 & 2:30-3:30 \n  \nDescription: Scouts looking to learn about animals and their habitats look no further and join us for an afternoon meeting live animals from Eyes of the Wild Exotic Animal Rescue. An Animal Educator will share fascinating facts about where these animals live and what makes each one so unique. Topics discussed at this event relate to animal themed badges for various girl scout levels. This program is held indoors\, with an outdoor self-guided scavenger hunt before or after the program (weather permitting).  \nFee: $10 per scout\, $5 per adult chaperone. Minimum 2 adult chaperones per troop.  \nRegistration Information: \n-Reservation requests open on February 11th at 9 AM. \n-Registration by Troop Leaders only – No individual scout registrations \nTo request a spot for your troop: \n1 – Complete Information by clicking on the link below starting  on February 11th at 9 AM. \n2 – Payment link will be emailed to you as space allows on a first come first serve basis.
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/scout-program-animal-program/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Events,Children
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2025/07/animalwithtrainer-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
