CREATED:20260227T005634Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260227T005634Z
UID:10138188-1772910000-1772915400@montclairlocal.news
SUMMARY:Bloom Where You are Planted: An Evening of Hopeful Songs
DESCRIPTION:Bloom Where You Are Planted: An Evening of Hopeful Songs is a concert event conceived by singer\, writer\, and board-certified music therapist\, Daniel James Belnavis. The night will consist of songs and stories by Belnavis\, a Montclair\, NJ native\, whose performance credits include Hamilton: An American Musical (Angelica Tour); Dreamgirls (Japanese Tour); and Violet (Boston’s SpeakEasy Stage Company). \n​Hope\, as well as resistance\, will be the through-line of the evening’s music\, with Belnavis singing an array of covers of uplifting songs\, both popular and lesser known\, that speak to the harrowing times we are living through. Belnavis’s wish is for Bloom to serve as a container that provides a sense of calm\, understanding\, respite\, and\, most importantly\, community in the midst of turbulent times. \nBloom will be held in the stunning sanctuary of First Congregational Church of Montclair\, an open and affirming church\, with a rich history rooted in abolition and inclusion. \n​Admission for the event is free\, however donations are much appreciated! Proceeds will benefit both The FCC Olmsted Garden and the American Friends Service Committee’s New Jersey Immigrant Rights Program in Newark. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/bloom-where-you-are-planted-an-evening-of-hopeful-songs/
LOCATION:First Congregational Church of Montclair\, 40 S. Fullerton Avenue\, Montclair\, NJ\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Art & Culture
