SUMMARY:Black Women in Biopic: The Rebellious Life Of Mrs. Rosa Parks (2022)
DESCRIPTION:The Rebellious Life Of Mrs. Rosa Parks (2022) | TV-PG\, 
 101mins\n\nBeyond her historic role in the Montgomery Bus Boycott\, this 
 comprehensive dive into Civil Rights icon Rosa Parks sheds light on her 
 extensive organizing\, radical politics\, and lifelong dedication to 
 activism. Watch the trailer here.\n\n\nSeating for the film is first come\, 
 first served. No registration is required.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult Services, Books, Film & Theater
UID:LibCal-10306-16233352
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16233352
