SUMMARY:SMC Annual Public Meeting
DESCRIPTION:South Mountain Conservancy Activities Meetup Group\nJoin us at
  our Annual Public Meeting to learn about the Conservancy's accomplishment
 s and 2026 programs directly from the program coordinators and discover ho
 w you can get involved and volunteer.\n\nRepresentatives from Trash Tacker
 s\, Trailkeepers\, Chainsaw Gang\, Citizen Science\, Hiking and Fairy Trai
 ls\, as well as board members\, will be available to answer questions and 
 share plans for the upcoming season.\n\n**Featured Speaker:** Don Weise of
  the [NY-NJ Trail Conference](https://somocon.us10.list-manage.com/track/c
 lick?u=52f0cff11223d2abc3a515cc9&id=924f32f69c&e=8d19458e7d) will speak on
  "Great Hikes and Less-Traveled Trails in North Jersey." Find out about ne
 w places to explore away from the beaten path! Don has extensive experienc
 e as a hiker and runner and just completed a new book on *Circuit Hikes in
  Harriman.*
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/somocon/events/313203897/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260204T134201Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260204T134201Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
