X-SOURCE-ID:montclairfoundation_calendar_of_events
X-SOURCE:Montclair Foundation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T210000
DTSTAMP:20260301T222716
CREATED:20260224T220154Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260224T220154Z
UID:10007134-1773255600-1773262800@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Virtual Meditation
DESCRIPTION:Virtual Meditation \nInstructor: John Welshons \nWednesdays\, 7:00 PM – 9:00 PM \nJanuary 7\, 14\, 21\, 28 \nFebruary 4\, 11\, 25 \nMarch 11\, 18\, 25 \nApril 1\, 8\, 15\, 22\, 29 \nJoin contemporary spiritual teacher and author Ramananda John E. Welshons (One Soul\, One Love\, One Heart\, When Prayers Aren’t Answered and Awakening From Grief) for a series of evening meditation classes in the comfort of your own home via Zoom. These classes will focus on specific practices for working with fear and anxiety.  Participants will learn and practice different forms of mindfulness meditation in each session and will have the opportunity to participate in discussions of Ramananda’s three critically acclaimed books. Open to beginners and experienced practitioners\, these gatherings offer an opportunity to experience deep inner peace while practicing with a highly experienced meditation teacher. \nImportant Updated Registration Information: \nA Zoom Link will be sent the day of the class. If you are registering after 3 PM on the day of the class\, the Zoom link will be included in the automated payment confirmation email sent when you register. There is no registration deadline for this class. \nFee: Single class: $10 Members / $15 General Public
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/virtual-meditation-32/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Events,Adults,Virtual
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2025/01/Magnolia-brooklyensis-_Yellow-Bird.jpg
END:VEVENT
