SUMMARY:Yoga @ the Library (Tweens & Grownups)
DESCRIPTION:Wrap up the week with a refreshing yoga session for tweens and 
 their grownups! (No unaccompanied grownups\, please.) Instructor Brittany 
 Martorella will lead you through gentle yoga poses and breathing exercises 
 to help achieve inner peace. Registration required.\n\nParticipants should 
 wear socks and bring their own bath/beach towels or yoga mats.\n\nMeet your 
 instructor:\nBrittany Martorella is a seasoned yoga teacher with over a 
 decade of experience honing her craft. Originally certified by Yoga to the 
 People in NYC\, Brittany's journey has led her to share her expertise 
 internationally\, from the bustling streets of NYC and Brooklyn to the 
 serene landscapes of Costa Rica\, where she studied and taught at Peace 
 Retreat. Specializing in Vinyasa\, Brittany's classes offer a dynamic blend 
 of movement and breath\, invigorating the body and soothing the soul. Her 
 love for restorative postures provides students with a chance to deeply 
 relax and rejuvenate.\nWith her infectious laughter\, she loves to remind 
 her students that yoga is meant to be fun. She creates an atmosphere of 
 light-heartedness and levity\, setting the stage for true calm and zen 
 focus in every class. Join Brittany on the mat and let's laugh\, flow\, and 
 grow together!\n\nSign up for the Monthly Teen Newsletter\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Programs, Fitness, Health & Wellness, Personal Growth, Teen Services
UID:LibCal-10306-15763526
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15763526
END:VEVENT
