CREATED:20260205T163158Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260205T163510Z
UID:10006740-1774083600-1774087200@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Spring Birding Class - Migration
DESCRIPTION:FREE Spring Birding Classes – Adults \nExplore the world of birds in the beautiful gardens of Van Vleck. Each class will focus on a specific topic to help us learn more about these amazing creatures. Weather permitting\, a birding walk will be included so bring your binoculars (or borrow a pair from Van Vleck) and join us for some birding fun. Instructor: Naturalist Jenny Aley\, Van Vleck Education Volunteer. \nMarch 21st – 9:00 AM -10:00 AM – Migration – Learn about migration and look for birds who are just passing through. \nOpen to adults. Space is limited – register early.   \nFree – Registration required – no drop-ins for this class. \n \nMay 12th  – 9:00-10:00 AM – Birds and their Nests – Examine various bird nests and look at how birds prepare for their new families. \nJune 27th – 9:00-10:00 AM – Young Birds – Sharpen your identification skills by focusing on young birds who don’t look exactly like adults yet.
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/spring-birding-class-migration/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2026/02/cranes-9858983_1280.webp
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Montclair Foundation": "https://montclairfoundation.org/event/outdoor-adventures-spring-has-sprung/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:montclairfoundation_calendar_of_events
X-SOURCE:Montclair Foundation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T120000
DTSTAMP:20260301T222716
CREATED:20251211T202418Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260116T204004Z
UID:10005972-1774087200-1774094400@montclairfoundation.org
SUMMARY:Outdoor Adventures: Spring Has Sprung
DESCRIPTION:March 21st – Spring has Sprung \nSaturday\, 10:00 AM – 12:00 PM \nJoin us as we celebrate the spring equinox at our March Outdoor Adventures program. Together we will explore the changes this season brings\, what plants are starting to bloom in the gardens\, and what wildlife we find in the springtime.   \nOn our Outdoor Adventures\, you and your family explore and learn about the outdoor world through crafts\, scavenger hunts\, activity sheets and educational displays. Each program will focus on a specific theme\, and our Van Vleck Education team will guide your family through this interactive learning experience. This program is entirely outdoors\, weather dependent. Registration is required and includes everything you need to participate in the program. Designed for children ages 4 -11 but all are welcome. \nFee: FREE for Members of Van Vleck; $15 per family  for  General Public \nRegistration required by 1 day prior to each class \n \nSponsored by  \n  \nUpcoming Outdoor Adventures \nApril 11th – Arbor Day Everyday \nArbor Day is a day to reflect on the importance of trees in our environment. We have an abundance of beautiful trees throughout the gardens. At April’s Outdoor Adventures\, learn more about our trees as we explore their role in our environment\, their unique leaf shapes\, and what animals use trees as their homes.  \n  \nMay 16th – Honeybees & Hummingbirds \nWhat do bees and hummingbirds have in common? They fly and they are pollinators! Join us to learn about your local pollinators\, how they make a positive impact on our environment\, and what we can do to help them on their mission.  \n  \nJune 6th – Insect Safari  \nYou can find many different insects buzzing\, wiggling\, and crawling around the gardens. Join us for an Insect Safari at this month’s Outdoor Adventures. Create a bug inspired craft\, take a hike looking for insects\, and learn about the important roles insects play in the garden.  \n 
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/outdoor-adventures-spring-has-sprung/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Children,Family
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2023/12/Crocus-tommasinianus-3-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Montclair State University": "https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12265374"}
X-SOURCE-ID:montclair_engage_events_ics
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:Athletics
DESCRIPTION:Take in classic Catskill views on this scenic hike to Balsam L
 ake Mountain via the Dry Brook Ridge Trail in the Balsam Lake Mountain Wi
 ld Forest. This moderately rated 6-mile out-and-back hike features a stea
 dy climb with 1\,197 feet of elevation gain\, winding through hardwood fo
 rests before reaching the summit. At the top\, hikers are rewarded with s
 weeping mountain views and a historic fire tower that offers a perfect sp
 ot to rest\, refuel\, and soak it all in. This trail is ideal for hikers 
 looking for a solid challenge with a big payoff.\nHow do I sign up?\n\nRe
 gister in the Student Recreation Center main office or over the phone (97
 3-655-3340).\nCost for Students $10 / Faculty\, Staff $20\n\nWhere and wh
 en?\n\nSaturday\, March 21\, 2026\n10:00 a.m. – 5:00 p.m.\nBegins at the 
 Student Recreation Center\n\nWhat to bring:Water\, lunch/snacks\, sunscre
 en\, bug spray\, layered clothing (depending on weather)\, sturdy close-t
 oe hiking shoes or boots\nPotential Hazards:Uneven and rocky terrain\; st
 eep sections\; slippery surfaces (especially if wet)\; sudden weather cha
 nges\; sun exposure\; dehydration\; insect bites\; poisonous plants/aller
 gies\; wildlife encounters\; and injuries including sprains/strains\, abr
 asions\, lacerations\, and fractures.\n\nHosted by: Campus Recreation\n\n
 Additional Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/
 engage/event/12265374
DTEND:20260321T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260302T033127Z
DTSTART:20260321T140000Z
LOCATION:Student Recreation Center
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Balsam Lake Mountain Hike
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12265374
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12265374
X-HOSTS:Campus Recreation
END:VEVENT
