CATEGORIES:Fundraising
CATEGORIES:Fundraiser
CATEGORIES:Drop By
CATEGORIES:Casual/ Relaxed
DESCRIPTION:Each year\, our graduating class participates in a proud Class
  Gift tradition where members of the class invest in the University by su
 pporting areas of Montclair State University that are most important to t
 hem. We invite the Class of 2026 to come together to show your support!\n
 All gifts to Montclair count! Make your gift to any area of campus you fe
 el most passionate about – such as the Emergency Book Fund\, The Red Hawk
  Pantry\, your school or college\, The Fund for Montclair State or athlet
 ic program.\nYour gift will pay it forward for future Red Hawks and kick-
 start your philanthropic connection to Montclair.\n\nCommemorate your cla
 ss year! Make a gift of at least $20.26 and you’ll receive your customize
 d philanthropy cord to wear over your commencement robe. \nFor a gift of 
 $40\, celebrate this milestone with your family\, friends and colleagues 
 by having your message displayed on the screen at the Commencement you wi
 ll be participating in\, and receive a customized philanthropy cord.\n\nH
 ow do I get my customized philanthropy cord?\nCustomized philanthropy cor
 ds will be available for pick-up:\n\nTuesday\, October 28 from 1:00 – 3:0
 0 p.m. in the Student Center Lobby\nThursday\, November 20  from 1:00 – 3
 :00 p.m. in the Student Center Lobby\nTuesday\, December 2 from 12:00 – 3
 :00 p.m. in the Student Center Lobby\nBloomfield Campus Graduation Fair: 
 Wednesday\, December 10th from 12:00 – 6:00 p.m. in Deacon’s Den\, Talbot
 t Hall (for Bloomfield graduates only)\nMontclair Campus Graduation Fairs
 : Thursday\, December 11th from 10:00 a.m. – 7:00 p.m. in the Student Cen
 ter Ballrooms (for Montclair or Bloomfield graduates)\n\nGraduates can al
 so arrange to pick up their philanthropy cords in the Overlook Corporate 
 Center\, 150 Clove Road\, Little Falls\, NJ during business hours\, Monda
 y through Friday\, 8:30 a.m. – 4:30 p.m. Philanthropy cords can also be m
 ailed to those who cannot pick it up. The last day we will mail the cords
  is Monday\, December 22\, 2025 at 2:30 p.m. Please contact James Stewart
 \, Associate Director of Annual Giving at stewartj@montclair.edu or 973-6
 55-5328 to finalize options to get your cords for the Winter Commencement
 .\nEvery student has benefitted from donor generosity to areas of academi
 c support\, emergency funding for students and overall priorities to boos
 t students’ success every day. Thank you for paying it forward!For more i
 nformation\, please contact James Stewart\, Associate Director of Annual 
 Giving\, at 973-655-5328 or stewartj@montclair.edu.\n\nHosted by: FAN: Fu
 ture Alumni Network\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://mo
 ntclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12117649
DTEND:20260325T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260302T033127Z
DTSTART:20260325T170000Z
LOCATION:Student Center 2C03 - 2nd Floor Lobby
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:2026 Class Gift Tabling - Information and Philanthropy Cord Pick-Up
